<section id="command-portflush">
<title>PORTFLUSH</title>
<indexterm><primary>PORTFLUSH</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PORTFLUSH</command> <parameter>port</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Flushes either the input or output queue of the open port.
If <parameter>port</parameter> is 0, then the output queue is flushed.
If <parameter>port</parameter> is 1, then the input queue is flushed.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>

<programlisting><userinput>PORTFLUSH 1</userinput>
</programlisting>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
